{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> γεωργ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>to be a husbandman, farmer</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 805e, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 14.2, etc.; γ. ἐν τῇ γῇ 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.92; ἐν τῇ Νάξῳ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthyphro” 4c, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; γεωργεῖς ἐκ τούτων you <b>have become a landed proprietor</b> by these means (i. e. the fruits of treason), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.314: with _accusative_ _cognate_, γεωργίαν ζῶσαν γ.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] of pastoral nomads, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1256a35:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, οἱ γεωργούμενοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Aristeas  112. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>till, plough, cultivate</b>, πολλήν (i.e. γῆν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 592 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰς ἄλλας [νήσους] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.88; γεωργῶν τὰ ἐκείνων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.41 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, of land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 9(1).61 (from Daulis)\">Refs</a>]; χώρας γεγεωργημένης καὶ γεωργηθησομένης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 685.80 (from Crete)\">Refs</a>]; τὰ γεωργούμενα φυτά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 896a10. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> generally, <b>cultivate</b>, ἐλαίαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Geoponica” 9.2.6: hence, γ. ἔλαιον, οἶνον\">Refs</a>], <b>produce</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 49.36, compare “IG” 22.1100; τοῦ γεωργουμένου οἴνου “Geoponica” 6.7.2. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>work at</b> a thing, <b>practise</b> or <b>exploit</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.82; φιλίαν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.776b; τέχνην 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 6.6; τὸν ἱππόδρομον 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Orationes” 35.13 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>cultivate</b>, ψυχὰς δόγμασι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.348. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> of a river, <b>fertilize</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Philostrati majoris imagines” 1.11, “Ep.” 59, 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 2.28. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1090","accentedUnicode":"γεωργέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1091","matchingForm":"γεώργιον","stepTransliteration":"geōrgion","gloss":"farm field","_zh_tw_Gloss":"耕地","_es_Gloss":"campo de cultivo ","_zh_Gloss":"耕地"},{"strongNumber":"G1092","matchingForm":"γεωργός","stepTransliteration":"geōrgos","gloss":"farmer","_zh_tw_Gloss":"園戶","_es_Gloss":"agricultor ","_zh_Gloss":"园户"}],"shortDef":"to farm, cultivate","mediumDef":"to farm, cultivate <br /><b>to cultivate, till the earth,</b> <ref='Heb.6.7'>Heb. 6:7</ref>*","stepGloss":"to farm","stepTransliteration":"geōrgeō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"cultivar (la tierra)","_zh_tw_Definition":"耕耘 (來 6:7)","_zh_Definition":"耕耘 (来 6:7)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"canh tác.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"耕種的人","_es_Gloss":"cultivar ","_zh_Gloss":"耕种的人"}]}